\par \loch\af0\dbch\af31505\hich\f0 \'93\loch\f0 If I were them, I\hich\f0 \rquote \loch\f0 \hich\f0 d fear a trap,\'94\loch\f0 \hich\f0  Bronn said. \'93\loch\f0 \hich\f0 Why else would we be so open, if not to lure them in?\'94
\par \hich\af0\dbch\af31505\loch\f0 \hich\f0 Tyrion chuckled. \'93\loch\f0 \hich\f0 Then we ought to sing and send them fleeing in terror.\'94\loch\f0  He began to whistle a tune.
\par \loch\af0\dbch\af31505\hich\f0 \'93\loch\f0 You\hich\f0 \rquote \loch\f0 \hich\f0 re mad, dwarf,\'94\loch\f0  Bronn said as he cleaned the \hich\af0\dbch\af31505\loch\f0 grease out from under his nails with his dirk.
\par \loch\af0\dbch\af31505\hich\f0 \'93\loch\f0 Where\hich\f0 \rquote \loch\f0 \hich\f0 s your love of music, Bronn?\'94
\par \loch\af0\dbch\af31505\hich\f0 \'93\loch\f0 \hich\f0 If it was music you wanted, you should have gotten the singer to champion you.\'94
\par \hich\af0\dbch\af31505\loch\f0 \hich\f0 Tyrion grinned. \'93\loch\f0 That would have been amusing. I can just see him fending off Ser Vardis wi\hich\af0\dbch\af31505\loch\f0 \hich\f0 th his woodharp.\'94\loch\f0 \hich\f0  He resumed his whistling. \'93
