She was hungrier than I would have believed. We finished two whole chickens and part of a third, and drank a flagon of wine, talking. I was only thirteen, and the wine went to my head, I fear. The next thing I knew, I was \hich\af0\dbch\af31505\loch\f0 
sharing her bed. If she was shy, I was shyer. I\hich\f0 \rquote \loch\f0 \hich\f0 ll never know where I found the courage. When I broke her maidenhead, she wept, but afterward she kissed me and sang her little song, and by morning I was in love.\'94

